sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36993
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Type II Secreted Antifreeze Actuator in E. coli (10-Repeat)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 5'UTR, signal peptide, non-glycolated antifreeze protein, and terminator that will as whole transcribe and secrete antifreeze protein outside the cell membrane.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nathan Barnett, Meghan Bowler, Kian Torabian
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Based on the sequence from the white flounder, Pseudopleuronecta americanus.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence has a 10 repeating unit of "ANAAAAAALTA", which is extended from the regular 5-repeat.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 5' Bicistronic UTR (strong), does not include ATG start
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 5' UTR based on bicistronic junction architecture. First RBS is strong and drives expression of short leader cistron. Second RBS internal to first cistron control translation of gene of interest. Architecture is optimized so that downstream CDS for gene of interest does not have a chance to form a secondary structure with the 5' UTR. See BIOFAB.org for more information.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: c/o Vivek Mutalik et al. BIOFAB Emeryville

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36726
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: An N-terminus peptide that carries and delivers a protein outside of the cell membrane using the Sec Pathway.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nathan Barnett, Meghan Bowler, Kian Torabian
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This peptide is a genomic sequence from E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is an N-terminal protein that should precede the protein you would like exported.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36996
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The standard non-glycolated antifreeze protein (AFP) from the Pseudopleuronecta americanus. Begins with a chain of C's and is followed by 10 rough repeats of "ANAAAAAALTA". The codons have been optimized for E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nathan Barnett, Meghan Bowler, Kian Torabian
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Based on the 5-repeated Segment AFP from the white flounder, Pseudopleuronecta americanus.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence has 10 rough repeats of "ANAAAAAALTA", as compared to the natural peptide which has this sequence repeated roughly 5 times.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: E. coli RNA pol transcription terminator designed and tested by Guillaume Cambray at BIOFAB Emeryville. Based on the natural E. coli rnpB T1 terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Guillaume Cambray et al. c/o BIOFAB Emeryville
